The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 LML Ltd said it will raise capital from overseas by issuing foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCB) up to Rs 250 crore. The shareholders in an EGM have approved the issuance of FCCBs and that of 45 lakh shares on preferential basis to the Mauritius-based Morrington Investments Ltd. The EGM has also approved issuance of 20 lakh shares and 0.001 per cent non-cumulative, non-convertible redeemable preference shares up to Rs 125 crore to the existing lenders of the company.

 ICICI Lombard has structured the first ever weather insurance cover for a maximum sum insured of Rs 1.5 crore for Gujarat Heavy Chemicals in the event of loss of salt production due to unseasonal rainfall at its Nagapattinam salt production fields in Tamil Nadu. ICICI Lombard would pay Gujarat Heavy Chemicals an insured compensation of Rs 6 lakh, Rs 10 lakh and Rs 25 lakh per non-production day.

 SBI Life Insurance has launched a Keyman insurance policy to provide cover to key members of a company who are major contributors to profit and whose absence may affect the business. The main objective of this policy is to protect the company?s interest by reducing financial consequences because of the death of a ?keyman? and help increase loyalty among key employees in an organisation.

 CashTech Solutions, a subsidiary of US based Fundtech Ltd and leading provider of products and solutions in cash management, has unveiled its J2EE-based TransactCentral application, TransactCashIn back office system, aimed at the South Asian market.TransactCashIn will enable existing clients to migrate to a web-based system that provides advanced features like event notification and flexible reporting.

 Steel Authority of India Ltd (SAIL) has been adjudged the runner-up by the Institute of Cost amp; Works Accountant of India (ICWAI) for its National Award for Excellence In Cost Management 2004. SAIL had received the winner?s trophy last year for excellence in cost reduction.

